The paper focuses on real-time deep learning for video-based facial performance capture, which involves computer vision and graphics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also mentions the use of multi-view stereo tracking, which falls under the category of computer graphics (cs.GR). Additionally, the paper involves machine learning techniques, specifically deep convolutional neural networks, which could fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper mentions the potential applications in video games and films, which could fall under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
